text.section:
The membership of the council shall consist of:
The secretary of the Justice and Public Safety Cabinet, who shall serve as the chair;
The Attorney General or his or her designee;
The chair of the Judiciary Committee of the House of Representatives or his or her designee;
The chair of the Judiciary Committee of the Senate or his or her designee;
The executive director of the Administrative Office of the Courts or his or her designee;
The president of the Kentucky Association of Criminal Defense Lawyers or his or her designee;
The deputy secretary of the Justice and Public Safety Cabinet, who shall serve as the deputy chair;
The commissioner of the Department of Kentucky State Police or his or her designee;
The commissioner of the Department of Criminal Justice Training or his or her designee;
The commissioner of the Department of Corrections or his or her designee;
The commissioner of the Department of Juvenile Justice or his or her designee;
A representative of the County Attorneys Association;
The Public Advocate of Kentucky or his or her designee; and
A representative of the Commonwealth's Attorneys Association.
